      "name": "FIRESTARTER Backdoor",
      "description": "CISA and the United Kingdom National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) assess that FIRESTARTER\u2014a backdoor that allows remote access and control\u2014is part of a widespread campaign that afforded an advanced persistent threat (APT) actor initial access to Cisco Adaptive Security Appliance (ASA) firmware by exploiting CVE-2025-20333 [ CWE-862: Missing Authorization ] and/or CVE-2025-20362 [ CWE-120: Classic Buffer Overflow ].",
